# Trading Engine — Cline Rules

## Project Type
Python algorithmic trading engine. Deployed on remote VPS via SSH.

## Code Style
- Python 3.12, type hints preferred
- Use `loguru` for logging (imported as `from utils.logger import log`)
- Use `pathlib.Path` for file paths
- JSON for data persistence (no database)
- All times in IST (Asia/Kolkata)

## Critical Constraints

### Strategy Code
- ALL strategies MUST inherit from `strategies.base.BaseStrategy`
- Implement: `should_enter(df, i)`, `should_exit(df, i, pos)`, `min_bars()`
- Use `.iloc[i]` for DataFrame row access — NEVER `df['col'][i]`
- Register in `strategies/registry.py` to make available to both backtest and live

### Files to NEVER modify
- `config/.env` — credentials
- `data/paper_portfolio.json` — live state (modify via portfolio_tracker API only)
- `core/strategies.py` — DEAD, do not resurrect
- `core/meta_allocator.py` — DEAD, do not resurrect
- `backtest/engine.py` — DEPRECATED, use backtest/unified.py

### Files that are the source of truth
- `strategies/registry.py` — what strategies are active
- `strategies/base.py` — how strategies work
- `backtest/unified.py` — how strategies are tested
- `jobs/swing_scanner_v2.py` — how signals reach the portfolio
- `execution/portfolio_tracker.py` — how P&L is tracked

### Metrics Rules
- Sharpe ratio requires minimum 30 trades (set `sharpe_valid=False` below)
- Primary metrics: CAGR, Expectancy, Profit Factor, Max Drawdown
- Transaction costs: 0.2% round-trip per trade (India: STT + brokerage + slippage)
- SELL signals rejected for cash equities (not shortable without F&O in India)

### Testing
- Test on 100+ stocks minimum (NIFTY100_PLUS in backtest/unified.py)
- Walk-forward validation required before trusting any strategy
- Portfolio tracker must survive type mismatches (use _safe_float/_safe_int)

